  "commentary": "With SPX at 6566.87 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-8.4B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+4.8B), dealers are likely buying the current level as we're above the major amplifying wall at 6550. The breakout regime with -34B total GEX means any push toward 6600 will face dealer selling pressure, while a break back below 6550 triggers aggressive dealer buying that could accelerate moves lower. Watch 6550 as the critical pivot—above it, dealers provide support; below it, they amplify downside momentum toward the 6500 level.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550 support and 6600 resistance with dealers amplifying any breakouts from this range.",
